WEBVTT

00:03:58.879 --> 00:04:01.717
It confronts us with profound questions,

00:04:01.741 --> 00:04:04.884
questions we might be too lazy
or distracted to ask

00:04:04.908 --> 00:04:06.581
in times of relative comfort.

00:04:07.047 --> 00:04:08.610
How should we work?

00:04:08.634 --> 00:04:09.947
How should we live?

00:04:10.766 --> 00:04:13.005
All of us, whether we realize it or not,

00:04:13.029 --> 00:04:14.601
seek answers to these questions,

00:04:14.625 --> 00:04:17.790
with our ancestors
kind of whispering in our ears.

00:04:19.020 --> 00:04:23.143
My great-grandfather
was a drunk in Detroit,

00:04:23.167 --> 00:04:25.730
who sometimes managed
to hold down a factory job.

00:04:26.611 --> 00:04:29.527
He had, as unbelievable as it might sound,

00:04:29.551 --> 00:04:31.422
21 children,